Sales Director (SD) - INDONESIA
Roles and Responsibilities:
Represent the Company's Intellect Products (cross business unit) to uncover
Help country manager to draw a sound business strategy
Develop a plan to identify competitively installed accounts and drive competitive displacements
Achieve / exceed sales targets as assigned
Identify and develop "pipeline generation" activities
Deliver sales presentations that drive account development in targeted clients and prospects.
Stay current on Company solutions products and offerings and maintain the appropriate level of solutions certification
Provide timely and accurate sales forecasts and utilize the Company opportunity management system to track pipeline of opportunities.
Provide inputs on pricing
Conduct negotiations on behalf of company
Attend project kickoff and ensure smooth hand-over to Project Management Team
Work closely with internal functional teams to ensure successful project delivery, service level agreements and maintenance support
Qualifications:
Minimum Requirements / Knowledge / Skills for AD
Degree/Master holder in Business
Minimum 15+ years experience and an overachiever of sales targets in the banking sector.
Deep understanding of banking operations and regulations.
Understanding of IT processes and implementations (functional and technical)
Has deep domain Knowledge of either retail or corporate banking
Is extremely well networked with senior management of all banks in the country
Hard working person
Monthly Salary Range: THB100000 - THB200000
Location: JAKARTA
Industry: Financial Technology Solution
